data.chText: 不诚实的；不正当的；不道德的
我们的关系没有什么不正当的。
data.enText: There was nothing improper about our relationship (= it did not involve sex) .

data.chText: 不合适的；不适当的；不得体的
data.enText: not suited or appropriate to the situation

data.chText: 在这个阶段发表评论并不恰当。
data.enText: It would be improper to comment at this stage.

data.chText: 他的衣着不大适合这个场合。
data.enText: He was improperly dressed for the occasion.

simple_means.memory_skill: im 不 + proper 正确的，适当的 → 不适当的

tr: not appropriate for a purpose or occasion
not suitable or right or appropriate
example: slightly improper to dine alone with a married man
improper attire for the golf course

tr: not conforming to legality, moral law, or social convention

example.ex: 25 officers were investigated following allegations of improper conduct during the murder inquiry...
example.tran: 25 名警察在被指控于调查谋杀案期间有非法行为之后受到调查。

example.ex: Mr Matthews maintained that he had done nothing improper.
example.tran: 马修斯先生坚称他没有做过非法的事情。

example.ex: I acted neither fraudulently nor improperly.
example.tran: 我既没有欺诈也没有犯法。

value.def: Improper conditions or methods of treatment are not suitable or good enough for a particular purpose.

example.ex: The improper use of medicine could lead to severe adverse reactions.
example.tran: 用药不当会产生严重的不良反应。

example.ex: The study confirmed many reports that doctors were improperly trained...
example.tran: 该调查证实了许多关于医生未接受充分培训的报道。

example.ex: He had become infected with Aids from an improperly sterilised needle.
example.tran: 他因使用消毒不当的注射针头而感染了艾滋病。

value.def: If you describe someone's behaviour as improper, you mean that it is rude or shocking.

example.ex: He would never be improper, he is always the perfect gentleman.
example.tran: 他总是举止得体,一直是个完美的绅士。

example.ex: Fundamentalist groups have attacked women they regarded as improperly dressed.
example.tran: 原教旨主义团体严厉抨击那些他们认为穿着不得体的女性。

trans: 不当行为；行为不当；出轨行为；不正当行为
处理不当；搬运不当；操作不当

rootsaffixes.indicate: = own, to own 自己的；拥有 , 引申为“恰当的”
rootsaffixes.title: prop(ri)

partsOfSpeech.dec: ap 加强 + propri 自己的；拥有，引申为“恰当的” + ate 做，造成，使… → 强行拥有〔公物〕→ 挪用
ex 除去 + propri 自己的；拥有，引申为“恰当的” + ate 做，造成，使… → 不再拥有 → 没收
im 不 + proper 正确的，适当的 → 不适当的
prop 自己的；拥有，引申为“恰当的” + er → 自己拿自己的当然是适当的 → 适当的
prop 自己的；拥有，引申为“恰当的” + er 表名词 + ty 表状态 → 财产；特性
propri 自己的；拥有，引申为“恰当的” + et + or 表人 → 拥有者 → 所有者
propri 自己的；拥有，引申为“恰当的” + et + ory …的 → 私有的
propri 自己的；拥有，引申为“恰当的” + ety 表状态 → 适当；礼节
